I make this recipe on a regular basis for entertaining or just to treat myself. When it's just for me to enjoy through a work week, I've simplified the recipe by using chix thighs, and instead of shallots, I use 1 bag of frozen pearl onions (thawed before sauteing) w/2 cloves of garlic near the end of sauteing. Its so much simpler that peeling all those shallots (and cheaper). I find the resulting sauce a bit flat so I finish with butter and white wine vinegar(after removing chix and veg. Just gorgeous. And I always serve over/with parmesan polenta(there's great recipe for it here on Epi)

