This is one of the better polenta recipes I've used. I added a little more cheese than called for, and, as it finished too soon for my entree, found that I could keep stirring in a little cream at a time to keep its creamy consistency. Served with garlic-herb pork chops and got raves from guests. Polenta (not just this recipe) typically is a little bland, so be sure to serve it as a counterpoint to something highly flavored.

Rating: 3
Really good. I'm just starting with polenta and often find it be bland and lacking. I too used 2 cups skim milk and 1/2 cup cream (I never have whole milk in the fridge it seems) and lots of cheese. I used a le creuset heavy pan and a silicone coated flat whisk and no scorching or sticking at all (I did have to stir in about a cup of boiling water halfway through cooking as it was getting wayyyy too thick). Delicious. One final note: unless you are using unsalted broth, the tsp of salt would likely be overkill (even the low salt broths are salty, and parmesan is as well).

