Rating: 2
I made this upon the recommendation of the Italian Chicken with Mushroom-and-Wine Sauce recipe. This was the first time I've made polenta, the second time I've eaten it. Polenta fans probably would consider this top-notch; even reduced-fat parmesan and 2% milk made it taste incredibly rich and buttery. I'm just not a polenta fan, though. BTW, add the cornmeal very gradually so that it doesn't clump together; I struggled to mash the clumps the rest of the time. Also, even though I whisked constantly, the pot bottom was covered with a stubbornly, cooked-on layer that took many soakings and scrubbings to remove - from a teflon pan, believe it or not.

